Postoperative Care for eye surgery.
1. The rest of the face can be mopped with a clean and wet cloth. Avoid splashing water into the operated eye.
2. You may use dark glasses during daytime and use eye shield for protection when you sleep.
3. Avoid cosmetics to the eye such as mascara, eye liners etc for at least 4 weeks.
4. Avoid driving till your surgeon gives you permission.
5. Avoided à¹ˆogging, swimming, gardening, contact sports until 4-6 weeks after surgery.
6. You may resume your sexual life a week or two after the surgery.
7. If you have any worsening of the symptoms and specifically if there is increasing redness, pain or decreased vision please hurry go to see doctor.